.TH "do_notify_parent_cldstop" 9 "do_notify_parent_cldstop" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
do_notify_parent_cldstop \- notify parent of stopped/continued state change
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" do_notify_parent_cldstop
.BI "(struct task_struct *tsk "  ","
.BI "bool for_ptracer "  ","
.BI "int why "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tsk" 12
task reporting the state change
.IP "for_ptracer" 12
the notification is for ptracer
.IP "why" 12
CLD_{CONTINUED|STOPPED|TRAPPED} to report
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Notify \fItsk\fP's parent that the stopped/continued state has changed.  If
\fIfor_ptracer\fP is false, \fItsk\fP's group leader notifies to its real parent.
If true, \fItsk\fP reports to \fItsk->parent\fP which should be the ptracer.
.SH "CONTEXT"
Must be called with tasklist_lock at least read locked.
